messageBody:
Hello Everybpdy,

This is my second attempt at posting to this group.
I am interested in determining if the time values generated by JUnit
3.8 are suitable for use in benchmarking the
unit under test.

We have experimentally determined that the setUp() times are included
in the time parameter. We are wondering of the tearDown() time is
similary included?

JUnit 4.3 looks very nice, and we are also wondering if the
use of the @BeforeClass/@AfterClass Annotations will prevent the
setUp/tearDown times being included.

This seems like a suitable question and it is not covered in the FAQ,
which was last modified in 2002.

Thanks all
